Anyone ever worked out a way to measure fuel flow and convert it into
real-time MPG? Some of the luxury cars dating back into the late 70's
and early 80's had them built into their computers and you could watch
the MPG on the digital readout on the dash. Seems like you could put
some sort of flow monitor between the filter and the carb that you could
interperet (based on your road speed) into MPG. Any idea how one would
rig it on a fuel injection setup to take into account the rate of return
flow to the tank? Hey, if James Bond can have an invisible car, why
can't I have a MPG meter! 
